text: North Jutlandic Island (Danish: Nørrejyske Ø or Vendsyssel-Thy) is the second- largest island of Denmark. About 297,000 people were living on this island in 2014. It has an area of 4,685 km². North Jutlandic Island lies on the south coast of the Skagerrak. It is the most northern part of Denmark, and is commonly regarded as part of Jutland.
